.TH CANMON 1 "2026-04-22" "canmon 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
canmon \- monitor SocketCAN / CAN\-FD interface state, configuration, and bit\-error rate
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B canmon
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B canmon
polls every CAN interface on the host (or the subset given via
.BR \-\-ifaces )
at a configurable interval and emits a line per interface per tick showing
the CAN error state, bitrate, per\-second error deltas, and notable events:
state transitions, configuration changes, auto\-restarts, and ticks in which
the CAN controller bit\-error rate exceeds a threshold.
.PP
All data comes from
.BR ip (8)
(via the
.B \-j \-details \-statistics
options) and
.B /sys/class/net
— no root required, no traffic interference, no dependency on
.BR berr\-reporting (8).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-ifaces " " \fILIST\fR
Comma\-separated list of interfaces. Default: every CAN interface.
.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-rate " " \fISECONDS\fR
Tick interval. Default: 1.0.
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-err\-rate " " \fIN\fR
Flag ticks in which the CAN controller bit\-error counter
.RB ( info_xstats.bus_error )
advances by more than
.I N
per second. Default: 1.
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-once
Print a single tick, then exit.
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-log\-only
Suppress the periodic table line; only print ticks in which an event occurred
(state change, config change, restart, or threshold flag).
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print version and exit.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help and exit.
.SH OUTPUT
Columns:
.TP
.B TIME
Local wall\-clock time of the tick (HH:MM:SS).
.TP
.B IFACE
Interface name.
.TP
.B STATE
CAN error state:
.BR ERROR\-ACTIVE ,
.BR ERROR\-WARNING ,
.BR ERROR\-PASSIVE ,
or
.BR BUS\-OFF .
.TP
.B BITRATE
Nominal bitrate, or nominal/data for CAN\-FD.
.TP
.B "Δerr/s"
Frame\-level rx+tx error delta per second (from
.BR stats64 ).
.TP
.B "Δbus/s"
CAN controller bit\-error delta per second (from
.BR info_xstats.bus_error ).
.TP
.B restarts
Running total of driver\-initiated auto\-restarts after bus\-off (requires
.B restart\-ms
to be non\-zero at configure time).
.TP
.B notes
Pipe\-separated event tags:
.B STATE old→new
on error\-state transition;
.B CONFIG old→new
on bittiming change;
.B RESTART #N
on auto\-restart;
.B BIT\-ERRORS N/s > T/s
when the threshold is breached.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Default 1 Hz monitor of all interfaces:
.B canmon
.TP
Sub\-second monitor, flag anything above 5 bit\-errors/sec:
.B canmon \-r 0.5 \-t 5
.TP
Events only, single interface, forever:
.B canmon \-l \-i can0
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR canconf (1),
.BR ip\-link (8),
.BR candump (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Dr. Michael Lauer <mickey@vanille-media.de>
